# nanoGPT environment variables — copy to `.env` and edit:
#     cp .env.example .env
#
# The Makefile auto-loads `.env` (via `-include .env`), so every KEY=VALUE here
# works two ways:
#   * Makefile config keys (DEVICE, COMPILE, GPT2, ...) override the defaults.
#   * runtime keys (DEBUG_SHAPES, PYTORCH_ENABLE_MPS_FALLBACK, WANDB_*, ...) are
#     exported into the python process the Makefile launches.
# If you run the scripts WITHOUT make, load it yourself first:
#     set -a && source .env && set +a
#
# FORMAT: plain KEY=value, no quotes, no spaces around `=`, no `export`
# (this file is parsed by both make and the shell).

# ---- debugging: print tensor shapes (shapes_demo.py / model.py dbg edits) ----
# 1 = print the shape of every step on the first forward pass, then stay quiet
DEBUG_SHAPES=0

# ---- Apple Silicon: only relevant when DEVICE=mps ----
# let the few ops MPS doesn't implement fall back to CPU instead of crashing
PYTORCH_ENABLE_MPS_FALLBACK=1

# ---- Makefile config overrides (uncomment to change defaults) ----
# DEVICE=cpu             # cpu | cuda | mps
# COMPILE=False          # True needs CUDA/Triton; keep False on Mac
# CONFIG=config/train_shakespeare_char.py
# DATASET=shakespeare_char
# OUT_DIR=out-shakespeare-char
# GPT2=gpt2              # gpt2 | gpt2-medium | gpt2-large | gpt2-xl
# INIT_FROM=resume       # resume (local ckpt) | gpt2* (pretrained)
# NUM_SAMPLES=5
# MAX_NEW_TOKENS=500
# (tip: prompts with spaces are easiest on the CLI: make inference START="Hi there")

# ---- HuggingFace cache: where `make download` stores GPT-2 weights ----
# HF_HOME=/path/to/hf-cache

# ---- Weights & Biases logging (only used if you set wandb_log=True) ----
# WANDB_API_KEY=your_key_here
# WANDB_MODE=offline     # offline | online | disabled
# WANDB_PROJECT=nanogpt

# ---- CPU threading (optional tuning) ----
# OMP_NUM_THREADS=8
# TOKENIZERS_PARALLELISM=false

# ---- Distributed training: set AUTOMATICALLY by `torchrun`, do NOT set here ----
# (listed for reference only — train.py reads these to detect multi-GPU runs)
# RANK= LOCAL_RANK= WORLD_SIZE= MASTER_ADDR= MASTER_PORT=
# on clusters without Infiniband, prepend NCCL_IB_DISABLE=1 to the torchrun command
